Reasoning: The paper presents a framework for incorporating approximate message passing methods in general graphical models, which involves partitioning dependencies into strong and weak edges and applying AMP approximations to aggregates of many weak edges. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Signal Processing (cs.SI), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper specifically mentions group sparsity and multinomial logistic regression problems as examples of the proposed methodology, which further supports the likelihood of belonging to these sub-categories.
